	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've built and programmed a Simon game on Arduino, It's my first actual &quot;game&quot; that I've made. I have footage here: <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1XBw2TR2Js8KKfgNw91ymBN37vs4CxZhi/view?usp=sharing" class="postlink">https://drive.google.com/file/d/1XBw2TR2Js8KKfgNw91ymBN37vs4CxZhi/view?usp=sharing</a> I'm debating wether or not I should share the schematics and the code publicly. if you have any recommendations for how I could make it better, please tell me. I feel like the wires could have been cleaner, as well as the whole thing could have been smaller, but that's the problem with using a breadboard.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
