	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Not bad! You can get a lot cleaner with a strip board which is also good to practice your solder skills on - but then again, you'll end up stacking projects because they're cumbersome to salvage. <br /><br />Little project pcb:s for things you might need is a good way to practice, too. Maybe you need another headphone amp, timer or interactive christmas lights or something?<br /><br />You're not a terribly long way from making a flipper game... though that effort requires a lot of space, time, interest, a bit of money to burn, and madness  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" />

		

